text:
When I saw this I wanted to cryğŸ˜­
To give more context... My grandma passed away on christmas of 2020 and we wanted to have her funeral asap. After her service was over, we got into our car and the radio automatically turns on but the song it played was ghost by justin beiber. So from that day on we dedicated that song to my grandma. I found skz in their maniac era and their music/chans room/skz code/ect. helped me through a lot and they have saved my life countless times. So knowing how much skz continues to save me, now the song that is dedicated to my grandma, was covered by one out the eight angels that saved my life. So thank you so much kim seungmin for covering this song it means so much to me...i love skz and i will always STAY with Straykids cause they have never failed to be their for meğŸ¥ºâ¤ï¸ğŸ¥²

author: @leashaanne
text:
I've been decided to make a cover of this song days ago, but then, something that I'll never want to happen come to me. On last Saturday, Oct 5 2022, my father passed away. That's my worst day ever, never expected it to happen, still can't believe my father was already gone, since he can pass his illness for almost 10 years. And this is also the first time I lost a loved one. Now this song will mean more to me after my father's passing. I also didn't expect all this coincidence, that I was going to make a cover for this song but then my father passed away and left me for good. 
May you rest in peace, dad. May God saves you in the best place. I already miss you so much. â¤ï¸

author: @h-playwithmyhart.4806
text: Seungmin, I would like to wish you an early happy birthday, as the time is drawing close. My introduction to Stray Kids was unique in that the reason I decided to support it was because of the fans. I have been a K-Pop fan for almost a decade, and I have come to support many groups. However, becoming a Stay was a new experience for me because it was the first time that I joined a group because the love from the fans was so strong, I knew I needed to be a part of it. I learned about each Stray Kids member one at a time, and what I learned and admired very quickly about you was your individuality. Every member stands out for their own reasons, but your charm is retaining your individuality and independence while still being a part of something bigger. I became an official Stay two years ago, and since then I have gotten to see how well you blend in with your members. You are such a valued member of Stray Kids, that we canâ€™t see them existing without you. Youâ€™ve also created a journey of personal growth and development both musically and personally and I have felt so connected to you since Iâ€™ve become a Stay. Your personality is so enticing in that sometimes you can be quiet and shy, but other times you are very vocal and humorous with your members. Itâ€™s very powerful that you can be so sweet and naturally kind-hearted without saying any words sometimes, while other times, being open and direct about how you feel. I can see how much your loving personality has impacted your members, because Iâ€™ve never seen them happier than when you spend time with them. You are always making your members laugh and motivating them just by putting one smile on their face. I feel so inspired watching you build such a trustworthy relationship with them and want to be at least half as generous as you. I know that your members are so thankful for you everyday and couldnâ€™t be anywhere near as successful without you. I have never heard a fanbase talk so highly and frequently of a member in the way that they honor you. I always hear Stay talking about how gentle and sweet you are; and how much positivity and love you bring to the world wherever you go. Stay talk about your rare, emotion-based, and versatile voice that captivates everyone into your performance. They talk about the flawless and effortless dancing that you work so hard to share with us and spoil us with on every stage. They talk about your overall professional and inspirational performance on stage that leaves every Stay wanting to spend more time with you. Iâ€™ve heard so much about how beloved you are Seungmin, and once I became a Stay, I am seeing for myself how much you are adored all over the world. Not only by Stay, but the loving influence that you have on your members makes them and everyone that you meet a kinder and more loving person. Stay praise and speak so highly of you, that I canâ€™t say Iâ€™ve experienced a family this loving toward an idol. I just want you know how much love there is everywhere all around the world for you. You are the reason that so many people lift their heads up and keep going another day, including me. There is so much negativity going on in the world right now, and to have you as a role model and see it not preventing you from sharing more love is making the world even stronger and closer to restoring to its greatness. I really feel like we donâ€™t deserve you sometimes because your genuine strong heart is hard to come across these days. I hope that we can repay you even a little bit of the love youâ€™ve shown us in just a few years since your debut. I know you have worked so hard to be where you are and I donâ€™t even want to pretend to know how much youâ€™ve probably gone through. I just want to take this day, and every day afterwards to recognize and let you become aware of how much I, Stay, and your members really love you. I know that your parents and the rest of your family are prouder of you than any other person and they respond to every action you take with great respect, understanding, and love. Your members and family are so lucky to have you and I know that are thankful and appreciative of you every day. Thank you so much for sacrificing more than we know just to make us happy even a little bit. On behalf of your friends, members, Stay, and loving family, I hope that the love that you have given to this world is given back to you on this special day and every day in your future. Please surround yourself by the people that love you most, and let the love that we have for you give you the most fulfillment! I wish you nothing but happiness for you and your loved ones, and I pray that you all stay safe!! Happy birthday Seungmin!!! We adore you so much and we are so grateful to have such a bright light in our lives!!!

Your voice suits the guitar very well. I'm officially in love. I love you Seungmin.

I was a little surprised when I heard his pronunciation of the word "Ecstasy" as it is not an easy word to pronounce for a foreigner, especially a Korean. I did not mean to underestimate him, It's just that he would have practiced so much to perfect the pronunciation of the word! These little things just make me so proud of our Minnie. author: @jathurshi.m9004
text: ive been busy these past few days and didnt get the chance to keep up with skz (2kr, concert recordings, etc.) ive also been really mad, but not at skz, not at stay, not at the concerts. ive been mad at my country and mad at myself for living in sri lanka and not being to see them who i love so much. that lead to me just avoiding them on the internet to get rid of my jealousy? god it was the worst feeling ever, all i could do was cry and cry and cry over the reality that i cant meet them. but i just now realized i was wrong for everything. i avoided my *reason* over something so petty. while i know i cant stop being jealous over ppl living my dream, i will congratulate them and be happy for them for finding their happiness and helping stray kids find theirs as well. ive seen how our boys smiled and laughed seeing stay directly from those few concert videos i had the heart to watch. i know i wont be able to see them in this lifetime with the economic situation in sri lanka and my future combined, but. But. If i can't get close to them, i'll settle for this. thank you for everything you have done for me. i found home.

author: @doomsdaykingdom86
text:
I am a newer Stay, but I questioned his voice on Venom. It's steady, youthful, consistent almost giving Shawn Mendes vibes (idk who else to compare it to in the US). After that, I have wondered what he can actually do? I noticed that when he sings in English he has the most natural (American) sounding accent. 

He isn't my bias, but I sing his parts in their songs I like the most. To a point my non-kpop liking sibling thought he was my favorite. The thing is as an older Stay I learned in a short time how to appreciate all eight members. I have been carefully looking at his videos and fancams too. It seems to me that out of all the members Seungmin is the one that people kind of turn a blind eye to, and don't take seriously. It's a fact when his fancams compared to the other are always the lowest. 

Some times you need appreciate what you have... An apparently sweet young man who still has a ways to grow and learn in life. 

Perhaps NOW we will take that innocent face and sweet voice and, start to appreciate not only what he has given... But also, appreciate the talent we yet to see. I think a lot of us don't know what raw talent is still there that we haven't seen not only for Seungmin, but for many other of the Stray Kids. 

They cannot be the only K-pop group I like for a reason. I also feel they are now just getting started. Not to make this about other members, but I really am excited to see how far some of them can be pushed vocally. I know there is talent. Even though they seem to fit into roles I want to see things shaken up. Also, let Seungmin rap like on a serious verse in this new era. I want JYP to let them cultivate all their skills in earnest. 

Happy that Seungmin got a little spot light today. ğŸ˜

P.S. apparently JYP doesn't pay for singing lessons for them. All of them should have signing lessons paid for while in the dorms! Treat them well, because you never know how far they will take JYP internationally.  Remember at least internationally this is the start. I hope they are treated with respect and dignity not only by the JYPE, but by fans too.

Bottom line: your artistic choices and agility and ability as a singer to make these choices are absolutely amazing! Keep it up <3

author: @jackybaduria806
text: Seungmin, I'm so proud of you! I can't explain how proud I am of you! Watching you grow as a main vocalist over the past few years makes me so proud! You've always done so amazing! Seeing you work your hardest in your singing and to express your emotions well through it as well as pay attention to the message, it makes me so proud. You inspire me to work harder as a singer myself, too. You deliver your emotions so well. I couldn't be any more prouder. Also, wow... Justin Bieber is amazing. I love his songs especially in this album "Justice" and just seeing your love for it as well makes me really happy. Thank you for covering a really beautiful song! I'm always looking forward to more covers from you. More moments to hear you sing with your beautiful voice. I'm gonna listen to you sing for a very long time! You really slayed this cover, Seungmin. You really did. And I can't believe it but how did you do all this yourself? From the added back vocals to the adlibs to the harmonies? You really slay it all! You really are our main vocalist. Keep going, Seungmin! We're always here to support you!!!

author: @minksetti1168
text: It's amazing how Seungmin is so determined and such a hard worker to keep improving not just vocally but to expand his ability to the point of being comfortable enough to cover an English song, and to do it SO WONDERFULLY. He sounds so natural. It's something to applaud him (and the rest of skz) for because to sing in your first language is one thing as an artist, but to appreciate and expand your comfort zone music in a different language is amazing and imo, it speaks a lot about them as artists. They really see music as a universal language to be enjoyed, irregardless of what language it's sung in. But the effort to sound natural and true to the language is immense and I have to applaud him for being so diligent.
